    "Given the roughly two-year life-cycle of festival films (see Festival networks section), events in the first and last years have fewer possible festivals to link to, and the data set itself is much smaller in the early years, translating to a lower but unknown baseline chance of being linked.",
    "We use network methods to address the following research questions about the international film festival circuit: What are the structure and temporal dynamics of the international film festival network?",
    "How diverse is the programming of different festivals?",
    "Are there differences between the A-and B-list events?",
    "What factors predict connections between festivals?"
